This toolkit operates on and produces derivatives of:

1. **Qwen3.6-35B-A3B** by Alibaba Cloud (base model)
   - Licensed under Apache License 2.0
   - https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B

2. **DeepSeek V4 Flash / V4 Pro** (teacher models used in HAS data generation)
   - DeepSeek License
   - https://www.deepseek.com

This toolkit's MIT-licensed output (Lynn V4-Pro/Flash Distill model variants)
follows the **R1-Distill style Path B** approach:

  - Distilled student model card uses MIT
  - Base model attribution under Apache 2.0 retained
  - Combined work is derivative of both upstream licenses

For full base model license terms, see:
- Qwen3.6: https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B/blob/main/LICENSE

Components and dependencies:

- `compressed-tensors` (NVFP4 v8-RTN quantization) — Apache 2.0 (Red Hat / NVIDIA)
- `huggingface_hub` — Apache 2.0 (HuggingFace)
- `modelscope` — Apache 2.0 (Alibaba)
- `llama.cpp` (referenced for Q4_K_M conversion) — MIT (Georgi Gerganov / ggml-org)
- `transformers` — Apache 2.0 (HuggingFace)
- `peft` — Apache 2.0 (HuggingFace)
- `LLaMA-Factory` (training framework used for V4 Distill LoRA) — Apache 2.0

Each script file may include further attribution in its docstring where it
directly references prior art (e.g., evaluation rubric inspired by HumanEval,
4-gate framework derived from internal Lynn rigor practices).
